import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['normal'] = pd.to_numeric(data['normal'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='normal', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['normal'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of normal temperature?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_datetime(data['actual'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='day', y='normal', data=data, label='Normal Temperature')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='day', y='actual', data=data, label='Actual Temperature')
    chart.set(xlabel='Day', ylabel='Temperature (°F)')
    plt.title('How does the actual temperature compare to the normal temperature?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='day')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='day', y='difference', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['difference'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["difference"].median():.2f}')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the trend of the difference between normal and actual temperature?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_datetime(data['actual'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    data = data.sort_values(by='day')
    data = data[['day', 'forecast', 'actual', 'normal']]
    data = pd.melt(data, id_vars=['day', 'normal'], value_vars=['forecast', 'actual'], var_name='type', value_name='temperature')
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='temperature', hue='type', data=data)
    plt.axhline(y=data['normal'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Normal Temperature Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['normal'].mean()))
    plt.title('How accurate are the weather forecasts?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
